quote-9 and its Usage

-- quote-9 can be used as part of blog posts.

quote-9 and its Usage

Package Name:
fifthtry.github.io/bling/quote-9

quote-9 is a new conversation experince via using FTD lang:

To use quote-9 on your web package, add below into FPM.ftd file:

-- fpm.dependency: fifthtry.github.io/bling
-- fpm.auto-import: fifthtry.github.io/bling/quote-9

-- fpm.dependency: fifthtry.github.io/bling
-- fpm.auto-import: fifthtry.github.io/bling/quote-9
Once you add above lines into your web package, add quote-9 into your .ftd files:
Example code for -- quote-9
-- quote-9.quote-9: Dr. APJ Abdul Kalam

"All of us do not have equal talent. But, all of us have an equal 
opportunity to develop our talents."

-- quote-9.quote-9: Dr. APJ Abdul Kalam

"All of us do not have equal talent. But, all of us have an equal 
opportunity to develop our talents."

Output of above basic example:

All of us do not have equal talent. But, all of us have an equal opportunity to develop our talents.
Dr. APJ Abdul Kalam

How to create custom component, using default attributes?

FTD lang is flexible and you can define your custom names to the default component. Below are few examples of custom names:
-- quote-9 with custom name as e.g. blog-quote:
-- quote-9.quote-9 blog-quote:
optional caption title:
body body: 
title: $title
body: $body

-- quote-9.quote-9 blog-quote:
optional caption title:
body body: 
title: $title
body: $body
How to use above custom name:
custom -- blog-quote usage:
-- blog-quote: Dr. APJ Abdul Kalam

"All of us do not have equal talent. But, all of us have an equal 
opportunity to develop our talents."

-- blog-quote: Dr. APJ Abdul Kalam

"All of us do not have equal talent. But, all of us have an equal 
opportunity to develop our talents."
